messages.messageBody:
**My mom had kids born in 1953, 1955, and 1959 and breastfed all of us.
Southern California. Was this really unusual? I never knew that.**

La Leche was founded in 1956. That year the breastfeeding rate in the US had
dropped to 20%. Rates didn't start climbing till 1972.

Yeah. It was unusual. :)

Deborah in IL
